            ; row 630 (2026-07-02, ~08:20): "yes, please" (lay the next stones).
            ; Laid model/ctc-logspace.fk — the CTC forward in LOG space, so
            ; real-length sequences do not underflow. Proven four-way (band 127):
            ; exp(log-p) == prob-space p where both work; and 10 frames of prob
            ; 1e-40 give prob-space EXACTLY 0.0 (underflowed) while log-space
            ; gives a finite -921. The reason it works is that log is the map
            ; turning products into sums — adding log-probs where the product
            ; underflows. The word for a structure-preserving map across spaces:
